cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the concept of fairness in machine learning applications, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the biases embedded in common understandings of fairness, which relates to the sub-category of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR). The use of welfare economics and game theory concepts further suggests the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the application of the proposed approach to a binary classification problem indicates the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CY).
